<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Cyrnellus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cyrnellus" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Cyrnellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Banks contains 12 species in the Neotropical region, and is widely distributed in North, Central, and South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Morse, JC" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" publicationUrl="http://www.clemson.edu/cafls/departments/esps/database/trichopt/index.htm" refId="B49" refString="Morse, JC, 2022. Trichoptera World Checklist. http://www.clemson.edu/cafls/departments/esps/database/trichopt/index.htm" title="Trichoptera World Checklist." url="http://www.clemson.edu/cafls/departments/esps/database/trichopt/index.htm" year="2022">Morse 2022</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Cyrnellus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cyrnellus fraternus" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraternus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Cyrnellus fraternus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a distribution from the USA to Argentina, being the most widely distributed caddisfly on the continent (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.654.9516" author="Holzenthal, RW" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 566" refId="B31" refString="Holzenthal, RW, Calor, AR, 2017. Catalog of the Neotropical Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera). ZooKeys 654: 1 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.654.9516" title="Catalog of the Neotropical Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.654.9516" volume="654" year="2017">Holzenthal and Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, it has a known distribution in several regions of Brazil and in the Northeast is registered for the Caatinga and Cerrado domains (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15560/6.1.007" author="Dumas, LL" journalOrPublisher="Check List" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="7 - 9" refId="B23" refString="Dumas, LL, Santos, APM, Jardim, GA, Ferreira, N Junior, Nessimian, JL, 2010. Insecta, Trichoptera: New records from Brazil and other distributional notes. Check List 6 (1): 7 - 9, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15560/6.1.007" title="Insecta, Trichoptera: New records from Brazil and other distributional notes." url="https://doi.org/10.15560/6.1.007" volume="6" year="2010">Dumas et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" author="Takiya, DM" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 195" refId="B81" refString="Takiya, DM, Santos, APM, Pinto, AP, Henriques-Oliveira, AL, do Lago Carvalho, A, Sampaio, BHL, Clarkson, B, Moreira, FFF, Avelino-Capistrano, F, Goncalves, IC, Cordeiro, IRS, Camara, JT, Barbosa, JF, Souza, WRM, Rafael, JA, 2016. Aquatic Insects from the Caatinga: Checklists and diversity assessments of Ubajara (Ceara State) and Sete Cidades (Piaui State) National Parks, Northeastern Brazil. Biodiversity Data Journal 4: 1 - 195, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" title="Aquatic Insects from the Caatinga: Checklists and diversity assessments of Ubajara (Ceara State) and Sete Cidades (Piaui State) National Parks, Northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" volume="4" year="2016">Takiya et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="151 - 171" refId="B20" refString="Desiderio, GR, Barcelos-Silva, P, Souza, WD, Pes, AM, Azevedo, CD, 2017. Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records. Zootaxa 422 (2): 151 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" title="Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" volume="422" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). In this study the species distribution is extended, representing the first record for the state of Pernambuco.
</paragraph>
